  "notes": "Ilocano (Iloko / Pagsasao nga Ilokano) — Northern Philippine (Austronesian) language of Luzon. Latin orthography; the digraph ⟨ng⟩ is a single letter /ŋ/. Native morphemes write /u/ as ⟨o⟩ in the ultima and ⟨u⟩ elsewhere, so ⟨o⟩ is ambiguous between /o/ and /u/. ⟨e⟩ is /ɛ~e/ in the nuclear dialects and loanwords but /ɯ/ in native words in non-nuclear dialects. ⟨r⟩ is a tap /ɾ/, ⟨rr⟩ a trill /r/. Unstressed /a/ is [ɐ] outside final syllables; /i/ and /u/ glide to [j]/[w] before another vowel. Glottal stop is phonemic but generally unwritten (⟨'⟩ / hyphen where marked).",
